show_headers plugin for SquirrelMail


Author
=====
Christian Sauer (christian@endrun.org)


Requirements
===========
SquirrelMail, at least version 1.4.  May work for earlier version
(haven't tested...if it works for you, let me know!).


Examples
=======
If you would like to see what Spamassassin score a message got, you
should put the following listing in your options:
    x-spam.*:
this would show both "X-Spam-Flag:" and "X-Spam-Level:" headers (if
the message has them).


I like to see what mail user agent people use (just for giggles) so I
have listed in my options the following:
    user-agent:
    x-mailer:
